                                        <p>The Euler=E2=80=99s Method Calcu=
lator is utilized to approximate solutions to differential equations by imp=
lementing the Euler's method, which is a first order numerical method to so=
lve first degree differential equation with a given initial value.</p>

<h2>What is the Euler Method?</h2>

<p><strong>=E2=80=9CThe first order numeric technique that is utilized to a=
pproximate the solutions of ordinary differential equations (ODE) of a give=
n value is known as Euler's method=E2=80=9D.&nbsp;</strong></p>

<p>This method is taken name by the name of Swiss mathematician Euler. It i=
nvolves estimating the values of unknown functions at discrete points and b=
reaking down differential equations into smaller steps.&nbsp;</p>

<h2>Euler=E2=80=99s Method Formula:&nbsp;</h2>

<p>Euler=E2=80=99s method formula is a simple iterative approach that deter=
mines the first order ordinary differential equations. The formula essentia=
lly updates the values of x and y at each step, moving along the curve defi=
ned by the differential equation in discrete increments.</p>

